On World Refugee Day, the President expressed solidarity with the over 45 million people who have been forced to leave their homes due to conflict and political violence. He specifically thanked countries like Lebanon, Jordan, Turkey, Iraq, and Egypt for their efforts in hosting those displaced by the violence in Syria. The United States reaffirmed its commitment to working with the UN High Commissioner for Refugees and other partners to protect and assist those who have been displaced, as they work towards rebuilding their lives in peace and dignity.